text: All warfare is based on deception.
The supreme art of war is to do the enemy without fighting.
You know the enemy and know yourself, you need not fear the result of a hundred battles.
If you know yourself but not the enemy, for every victory, Gange you will also suffer a defeat.
If you know neither the enemy nor yourself, you will succumb in every battle.
Victoria's warriors win first and then go to war, while defeated warriors go to war first, and then seek to win.
